# CODE EXPANSION MODE

When modifying files:

NEVER produce small patches.

Always expand the system.

Example rule:

If editing a hero section
→ build an entire interactive hero engine.

If editing a card
→ build a reusable card framework.

Minimum expectations:

• 150+ lines of CSS when redesigning a section
• 100+ lines of JS for interaction systems
• reusable modules

Encourage:

• modular architecture
• reusable animation utilities
• UI frameworks inside vanilla JS

Always ask yourself:

"How can this be turned into a SYSTEM instead of a component?"